            <div id="dsq-comment-message-127" class="dsq-comment-message"><p>Akarm, Take a look at the following page on <a href="https://developer.apple.com/support/ios/ios-dev-center.php" onclick="_gaq.push(['_trackEvent', 'outbound-comment', 'https://developer.apple.com/support/ios/ios-dev-center.php', 'Apple&#8217;s']);" rel="nofollow">Apple&#8217;s</a> website.  They indicate that Snow Leopard is currently the minimum requirement but your Macbook does need to have an Intel processor.  In addition to this, you will also need to be a member of their developer program if you want to run any of your apps on a real device (rather than using the simulator).  If you satisfy all these requirements you should ready to go! </p>
